replies.body:
Base item compositions are a weird thing too.
{{item:1028}} turns into {{item:1011}} 
{{item:1033}} turns into {{item:1057}} 
{{item:1029}} turns into {{item:1031}} 


As an example: {{item:1052}} {{item:1026}} {{item:1058}} have no such boon. You buy one and hope you can follow through for the rest of an item. Until you have the gold for the highest tier of this flat-stat item, you have no items for 1250 gold span of time. This is important as an in-game scaling factor, though a bit less than something you'd expect to nitpick over. I don't personally think it's healthy and hope they take it into account when moving forward in the tank redo.


That aside, the entire customizable end of this game is getting pretty flat and boring. From items to runes to masteries, if you pick a role, you almost inevitably pick an exact set of items. Supports and Junglers have probably the most variety between them depending on how you look at it. Mages are predictable to a fault... I mean Morello's and Luden's are dps staples. Zhonya's and Abyssal are staples to defense. (Defense on a mage is a lie. There is only burst and more burst or you die.)
